cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses machine learning techniques to approach the NER tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural network models such as BiLSTM-CRF. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as named entity recognition is a common task in information retrieval.
